website_summaries.verdict: A sound buy if you want a model with ample work and storage space, but it offers less space for wine bottles than other contenders.
pros: Multipurpose features: shelves, wine glass hanger, wine bottle holder, removable drawers
Looks good and is easy to assemble
cons: It takes up a bit of space, and the construction feels somewhat flimsy

customer_reviews.title: I LOVE MY WINE RACK
customer_reviews.text: I LOVE MY WINE RACK!!!! NO QUESTION!!! But I did take another reviewers suggestion and buy some wood from home depot and add to rack to make a little more sturdy.... I also took it a step further and stain the wood. DID I TELL YOU, I LOVE MY WINE RACK! AND I LOVE ROYAL BLUE! FYI: the bottles going forward makes me nervous so I turned it the other way! Great Rack!
customer_reviews.author: Coya

customer_reviews.title: Great addition to my kitchen
customer_reviews.text: Easy to put together, no help needed. I got it to add storage space to my tiny kitchen. Its cute and does the job. Very sturdy which is great because I didn't want to keep storing my cast iron set inside my oven. Second item ive purchased from this seller and I'm very pleased.
customer_reviews.author: Jay V.

customer_reviews.title: Easy to assemble and looks great
customer_reviews.text: Super easy to assemble and looks great in the kitchen. The only reason I am taking away a star is because the middle slats on each shelf are really poor quality and bend with the slightest weight put on them. They don’t stay straight and sturdy. Otherwise, for the price, it is a great shelf for our kitchen.
customer_reviews.author: J. Wallace

customer_reviews.title: One basket not made right, ehat do i do, everything else is ok.
customer_reviews.text: First of all this item looks good, it fits in the area i needed, secondly assembling this item was easy, but when finish the assembling going to the baskets i noticed that one of the baskets were assemble wrong, as to now i really don't know what to do. Tried calling customer service but no answer after 6 try's, tried leaving a message but as to date no reply. So now i am stuck with a basket that cannot be used, and to return item i would have to tear down and repack for shipment. Please note the video attached.
customer_reviews.author: Cedric

customer_reviews.title: Attractive and great combination of items!
customer_reviews.text: I combined four items: 1) Sunblaster 904297 NanoTech T5 High Output Fixture Reflector Combo, 3-Feet 2) Tiffany Style Floor Lamp Arched Adjustable 62" Tall Stained Glass Red Yellow Floral Flower Tulips Antique Vintage Light Decor Bedroom Living Room Reading Gift AM073FL12 Amora Lighting 3) Celtic 3 Drawer Storage Shelf - Rattan Baskets w/ Wrought Iron - Black Finish 4) Two locally cut glass 1/4” shelves And the came up with an attractive way to grow plants and MicroGreens! I really like all these items when used together!
customer_reviews.author: speedyb

customer_reviews.title: love this rack!
customer_reviews.text: I love this rack! Purchased it to fit under our breakfast area since we don't use it. It holds our crock pots, toaster, and other kitchen items we don't use every day so we can save space on our counter. We love the design and colors, as well as the ease of putting it together. Extremely pleased with our purchase!
customer_reviews.author: Sophie

customer_reviews.title: Really nice looking, my neighbor bought one after seeing mine!
customer_reviews.text: PROS: It was a breeze to put together. I am using this as a shelf for plants placed next to tall windows. The plants love it! the storage below is very useful. It looks really good, and have had compliments on it. CONS: The lower shelf isn't solid nor is there a cover that could keep debris from above from falling directly into the baskets below. I bought clear plastic shelving for both selves, one to keep the interior of the baskets from getting dirty and bit of whatever in them, add secondly to stabilize smaller pots on the top shelf.
customer_reviews.author: agypsyfoot2

customer_reviews.title: ... fill a space with something visually tasteful but also useful. My only complaint is that one of the ...
customer_reviews.text: Bought this to fill a space with something visually tasteful but also useful. My only complaint is that one of the 3 wine-glass holder "racks" broke during assembly due to a poor spot weld between the bent wire and the mounting tab. This is minor to me as I didn't buy this for the wine-glass holding capability. It is still disappointing. Otherwise, the assembly went smoothly, instructions were good. Fasteners and tool to assemble were included in the box, which I always appreciate. The powder-coat finish seems nice too.
customer_reviews.author: K. Nielsen

customer_reviews.title: Cute but crooked.
customer_reviews.text: Great in theory, looks lopsided though. Space saving. Everything came labeled, no damaged pieces. Instructions are pictures only which could be frustrating for some. Overall, I'm too lazy to take it apart and send it back for a refund. Had I purchased in store for more than $30, I'd return. I think once I fill it with wine and knick knacks, no one but those with ocd will notice how crooked it is. The wood piece is a nice color but I'll probably be painting mine to match my decor.
customer_reviews.author: Debi!

customer_reviews.title: Customer  Service was great
customer_reviews.text: Had to contact customer service due to a part that broke during assembly and another part where the screw hole was not tapped properly. The lady I spoke with was very polite and helpful. Received replacement parts in about a week-week and a half. The unit it self is not the best quality but decent. Two people will make assembly much easier. You will need to deviate from the assembly instructions slightly in order for assembly to go smoothly. (Will explain if you ask). Wine glass holder does not accept standard wine glasses stem base and the top shelf is slightly torqued. All in all wife and I are happy with it.
customer_reviews.author: David Fulton

customer_reviews.title: Beautiful and Versatile
customer_reviews.text: I love it! It was exactly what I wanted. I put it together myself and it was so easy. I have my orchid plants on the top and peanuts for the squirrels in one of the drawers. I have received many compliments on the style. At first I put the bottom shelf on upside down, so look for the tracks the baskets slide on.
customer_reviews.author: Suzy Q

customer_reviews.title: Love it!
customer_reviews.text: Perfect for the "spa"look I wanted in my bathroom. I used the baskets on the middle shelf and did not install the bottom shelf since it would not be used because of the heat duct register on the wall interfering with it. It looks fantastic this way. Shipping was very quick, product was well packed, and it was very easy to assemble. Highly recommend and am extremely pleased with how it looks and fits in my bathroom. I personally like the dimensions and the size is elegant and unique.
customer_reviews.author: Rebecca C.

customer_reviews.title: Cute Wine Rack
customer_reviews.text: I love this wine rack. It holds plenty of wine for my needs and has two baskets that I can keep other wine related things in, including my stemless glasses and bottle openers and stoppers. The only downside is that the shelves are slotted so you have to be careful about sitting some items on the shelves. It was a little hard to put together and was glad I had assistance. You may have to tilt the glass to fit through the slot opening but no other issues with hanging the glasses. I'm very happy this item.
customer_reviews.author: Wesley

customer_reviews.title: This thing works great. Turned mine into a full on bar
customer_reviews.text: This thing works great. Turned mine into a full on bar. I purchased a couple Godinger silver serving trays to set on the top shelf, looks really nice. You can fit plenty of bottles of alcohol across the top. It seems pretty sturdy as well. The glass hanging holders are worthless, the openings are way to small for any base on the wine glasses i have...so i just took them off and again, added a couple serving trays to the shelves above the wicker baskets. Thing looks pretty good after putting some additional money into it.
customer_reviews.author: BWK

customer_reviews.title: You get what you pay for!
customer_reviews.text: Got it yesterday and it's going back as soon as I print out the labels. When one of the sides wasn't secure, I thought, no big deal....just kind of decorative. But when some of the screws couldn't be screwed in all the way, apart it came and back it goes. The only reason it gets 1 star is because I had to pick one. Don't waste your money
customer_reviews.author: Jill Koehnlein

customer_reviews.title: Need a little extra storage that's attractive and easy to assemble? You've found it!!!
customer_reviews.text: I was needing some extra storage space in my kitchen but didn't want anything tall as it would block my window. I happened to come across this and so I ordered. So glad I did. Wow! This little baker's rack is just perfect! It's very easy to put together--I did it myself and it didn't take long. Love how much counter top room this has freed up for me!
customer_reviews.author: mjneel

customer_reviews.title: ... is a really cute unit and we are really happy with the look
customer_reviews.text: This is a really cute unit and we are really happy with the look. We've gotten multiple compliments on it. My engineer husband put it together and it fits the decor of our dining room well. My only complaint is that it wobbles a little. My guess is this has been a problem for other people as well, because they included little brackets to attach to the wall to help with this. The problem is, then they provided white zip ties to attached the unit to the small brackets. Cheesy! We didn't use them obviously, and because our rack sit up against the wall we alleviated most of the wobble.
customer_reviews.author: hot pepper jeep

customer_reviews.title: LOVE THIS WINE RACK!
customer_reviews.text: I love this bakers/wine rack! I was very easy to assemble and it is the perfect size to make a little bar area in my small apartment. I am going to take other people advice though and purchase a piece of wood(probably pine) for on the top rack to studying up for putting bottles of liquor up there. The black slats are a little far apart and I worry if bottles don't get put there just right they will fall over. My glass holders work perfectly and the baskets are a wonderful touch for bar accessories!
customer_reviews.author: Lisa Barbee

customer_reviews.title: Don't waste the time!
customer_reviews.text: Complete JUNK! I normally don't write reviews, but want to save others from wasting their money and time. The assembly was a complete nightmare. The instruction book is simply pictures, but no detailed instructions. It's a guessing game as to which direction each piece was supposed to go. There was a "QR Code" inside to click for further instruction help. The QR Code led us to a website for assembly on fireplace inserts. The drill holes didn't line up. The unit ended up being un-level. I certainly couldn't utilize the shelves on the unit. Anything placed on them would fall off! We ended up taking the rack back apart, reboxing it, a sending it back for a refund!
customer_reviews.author: Heidi Sypin

customer_reviews.title: Looks nice!
customer_reviews.text: I love the wine rack - I bought this for holding some barware, wine, and generally for filling some empty space in my kitchen. I wouldn’t put anything heavy on this, but that’s not what I purchased it for anyway. Slightly shorter than I wanted, but it works. Easy to assemble with good instructions. It took me about an hour to put together by myself, and I’m only semi-competent at putting things together. It would be easier with two people, but it wasn’t difficult at all with just one. Styrofoam packaging wasn’t super crumbly either, which is always appreciated.
customer_reviews.author: E

customer_reviews.title: Gorgeous little wine bar.
customer_reviews.text: This piece fits so well in my small kitchen. I'm making it into a wine/coffee bar. It's a perfect height to sit underneath a window. I will be adding on the wood shelf pieces that a lot of other people are doing. The metal shelves just don't seem like a place I want to sit my crystal wine glasses. Seems dangerous. Easy to assemble. The instructions are immaculate, and they even provide more hardware than you need just in case you lose some.
customer_reviews.author: LeShae Nash

customer_reviews.title: Storage shelf
customer_reviews.text: I thought this would be MUCH bigger, but it is very small and short. The baskets are cool, and, as it turns out, I needed something about this size for where I was placing it. But it’s really small & short.
customer_reviews.author: E. Stewart

customer_reviews.title: Very Good Choice
customer_reviews.text: Bakers rack is just as it appears. It is well made with no rough edges. The baskets are large enough and sturdy enough for cookbooks. The shelves are sturdy and have open slates so you may need something solid on top depending what you use it for. Assembly was easy with pieces marked alphabetically and picture instructions easy to understand. Bought this rack with a narrow taller unit. Both were scrolled wrought iron with baskets. One color is black and one is gunmetal gray but they are close enough to be a near match. I was very pleased with this purchase.
customer_reviews.author: Kindle Customer

customer_reviews.title: It looks great, I've had many compliments on this piece
customer_reviews.text: I purchased this unit to use as a TV stand. I had (2) pieces of 3/8" plate glass cut to fit the two metal slat shelves. It looks great, I've had many compliments on this piece! Really easy to put together! Have ordered the matching baker's rack for my dining area, really looking forward to seeing that as well!
customer_reviews.author: Sharon B

customer_reviews.title: PRESENTS BETTER ON LINE
customer_reviews.text: PRESENTS BETTER ON LINE, BASKTES WERE RAVELING UPON DELIVERY, SMALER THAN EXPECTED AND THE QAULITY SI LESS THAN EXPECTED, THE BASKETS WEAVING IS NOT THE BEST AND COMES APART BUT I DO NOT WANT HASSEL OF RETURNING, I WILL JUST BUY BETTER BASKETS FOR IT
customer_reviews.author: Luvada Kay Guenther

customer_reviews.title: Missing holes for assembly, extremely cheaply made.
customer_reviews.text: I was astounded by the thinness of the pipe this is made from and that each pipe connection is only done with one tack weld. The wall of the pipe measured .023" with paint on it, meaning the metal is only 4-5 times as thick as a sheet of printer paper. I began assembling it just to see what it would turn out like and was unable to due to missing threaded holes in the tubing. It was a total waste of time and now I have to try to rebox it to send back.
customer_reviews.author: KeaC

customer_reviews.title: Lightweight and easy to assemble
customer_reviews.text: I was looking for a storage for my vegetables and fruits, The baskets at the bottom of the shelf contain enough room for my veggies and fruits. The baskets were a little hard to put, but the shelfs can be put together quickly. Looks sturdy and beautiful in the kitchen.
customer_reviews.author: Nidzie

customer_reviews.title: Buy it! You won't regret it!
customer_reviews.text: This has to be the easiest thing I have ever set up! It's sturdy and looks really nice! It fits on my side wall perfectly and it clears up space on my counter. Well worth the money spent! I may just have to get another one!
customer_reviews.author: Dawn Erickson

customer_reviews.title: Attractive Storage Shelf
customer_reviews.text: This was purchased for use in the entryway of our home to collect shoes pulled off as one enters the door. The assembly was easy and it is sturdy. I could have used this same item with one more shelf, but the company did not offer that option. The price was steeper than I wanted to spend, but this was the only storage unit I could find to meet our needs. Visitors and family comments have been very positive on the storage unit.
customer_reviews.author: Critique T

customer_reviews.title: Impressive
customer_reviews.text: From box to fully assembled in just under 40 minutes, I'm very impressed with this. Although the list price is somewhat over-inflated from their marketing department, it's still a very nice wine rack. The directions were well laid out and my only recommendation is that I would hand tighten all the screws during assembly and then put the final torque once the rack is fully assembled. Having to assemble the baskets was a cinch and in my opinion, having a metal frame makes them very sturdy and durable. Although Amazon was not able to provide a tracking number through the seller, it arrived five business days after I placed my order.
customer_reviews.author: VA Patriot

customer_reviews.title: If you like it in the picture then you will like it ...
customer_reviews.text: Looks exactly as the picture. If you like it in the picture then you will like it in your home. Not too difficult to put together
customer_reviews.author: Vincenza Di Meglio

customer_reviews.title: Easy to assemble
customer_reviews.text: This storage credenza is just the right size for my small breakfast nook and holds all of the packaged drinks in one place. it is sturdy, and loaded with drinks, stable. The kit includes a wall anchor system, but as I have no toddlers, we chose not to use because of the stability. Only took 10 minutes to assemble and it came with all the tools required, even extra bolts. Would buy again.
customer_reviews.author: Gail Brion

customer_reviews.title: Easy to assemble; fits and looks great!
customer_reviews.text: I am so happy with this wine rack! It was so easy to put together and it holds the wine bottles securely. It looks great in my dining room and the price was great! Upon reading other people's reviews, I definitely want to add a piece of wood to the top so that it isn't so un-sturdy. I have a few wine bottles sitting on it now, but if I shook it, they would fall. The baskets are great and fit perfectly at the bottom.
customer_reviews.author: Rachel K.

customer_reviews.title: I'm very pleased with this piece
customer_reviews.text: I'm very pleased with this piece. Thank you soooo much to the company for making the instructions easy to follow for someone like me. I put it together myself, without any help, a bit challenging, but it can be done. Sturdy and attractive piece. I'm very happy. Would buy from them again.
customer_reviews.author: nichole anderson

customer_reviews.title: Serves a purpose
customer_reviews.text: I really like the look of this and wanted something with baskets. The middle shelf is great to store cookbooks but if they're too tall they won't be able to stand up (lay them on their side). Overall, I like it but wish it were a bit larger. The assembly was easy.
customer_reviews.author: MacGirl29

customer_reviews.title: With the wood I'm very pleased
customer_reviews.text: I really like this wine rack. I ordered it Saturday and got it Sunday. The assembly was not hard at all. I followed the others suggestions and got some wood. I wanted to get Quartz but I didn't have the tools to cut it. Right now I have I have a birch 1/2 in thick plywood I got for $16 buck at Home Depot. I'll probably stain it later or try oak or another type of wood down the line. It is a bit wobbly but I bolt it to the wall and it's much sturdier. I am very please with this purchase. The Additional wood makes ALL the difference.
customer_reviews.author: Pinky

customer_reviews.title: Tiny and weak shelves.
customer_reviews.text: The item is much smaller than expected. The shelves are weak and sag when items are placed on them. Not at all worth $112.50. I am not happy with it.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: Love this storage shelf
customer_reviews.text: I had one of these a long time ago and was so happy to see they are still available. It is attractive, sturdy and easy to assemble. I think it looks great inside and outside.
customer_reviews.author: Michelle Chino

customer_reviews.title: Fermenting storage station
customer_reviews.text: I keep this in my kitchen as a Kombucha/fermentation table, I don’t have alcoholic drink at home but my family’s favorite drink it’s kombucha and I have to make gallons of it. looking for a place where I can storage them and some clean empty bottles and I find this very useful and convenient for my kitchen size.
customer_reviews.author: OR

customer_reviews.title: Wish I had read color in description
customer_reviews.text: It is a very nice shelf and extremely easy to assemble. The only reason I am giving 4 instead of 5 is really because of a mistake that I made. It appears black to me in the pictures and I didn't pay attention to the description, only the measurements. It's actually gray which doesn't look quite as good to me as black would. Nothing a little spray paint can't fix though. Oh, and it is a little wobbly. I'm sure once items are placed on it, it will not be. Gotta wait til I paint it though.
customer_reviews.author: AW 226

customer_reviews.title: Very nice
customer_reviews.text: It looks smaller than I thought, but it measures correctly. Very cute by my back door for hats, gloves, and mail
customer_reviews.author: jom

customer_reviews.title: But a better job could have been done on designing the shelves
customer_reviews.text: This is o.k. But a better job could have been done on designing the shelves. Would be better if they were solid as things would sit better, also could be more level. More space should have been given to the wooden shelf and the one above to allow more ease to pour a glass of wine. The hanging wine glasses are in the way.
customer_reviews.author: Beverly Smith

customer_reviews.title: Perfect Shoe Rack
customer_reviews.text: I purchased this last year to use in my laundry room. I also bought the matching bakers rack to hold a steam press I purchased to press jeans, skirts and things. They both are very sturdy. Both were easy to assemble, have a very nice appearance and fit great in the small space. They replaced some older style white utility cupboards...big improvement. The smaller shelf holds up to 20+ pairs of shoes in the baskets and on the shelf. It was perfect for my needs.
customer_reviews.author: Tea Bee

customer_reviews.title: Simple and Sleek.
customer_reviews.text: I was able to put this together in about 30 minutes with some help. My only complaint is that the holes didn't always match up. Alas, it looks beautiful, serves a wonderful purpose as a modest wine and liquor display, maybe some day I may turn it into a coffee bar instead. It blends perfectly with my small space. I found this product cheaper than many other competitors as well. This bar holds liquor bottles as well as wine bottles.
customer_reviews.author: J

customer_reviews.title: Nice finished item with modifications.
customer_reviews.text: Beautiful piece but wrought iron is more of a pewter gray color instead of black. The shelves have metal slats that seemed unsturdy. The wine bottle opening won't hold the slightly bigger bottles. But for the price, I'm satisfied.
customer_reviews.author: Lisa

customer_reviews.title: Nice but a bit pricy
customer_reviews.text: I really like the product it took me just over an hour to build all of it. the baskets were disappointing since they look like they are one piece however they are not, you have to put them together as well, and if you choose to put something it them it cant be very heavy since they are flimsy. It will do the trick for what i wanted but expected it to be a little more thicker for the amount I paid. if i had to do it again I would pay less then 100.00 to make it a good buy. I still love this piece regardless of how much I paid.
customer_reviews.author: CLARA A. PULIDOCASTILLO

customer_reviews.title: Good, Sturdy shelves
customer_reviews.text: I love this set of shelves! Don't plan to switch the wicker baskets out for something else. They're a custom size I cannot find anywhere. Also, you can't really decide not to use them. There is only one support bar under it so other items tend to fall right through.
customer_reviews.author: Scottie

customer_reviews.title: Space saver
customer_reviews.text: Great addition to small spaces....i gave as gift to my granddaughter and she loved it. Storing wine, wines glasses, & like items, gave her more room in her cabinets. I would recommend this bakers rack...
customer_reviews.author: Black Widow

customer_reviews.title: How do I get it back in the box?
customer_reviews.text: Its a lot smaller than expected and seems flimsy. It came bent in a few places, specifically the slates on the top shelf. They bow in and you can't flatten it out. I had to bend the wine racks back into shape and the track for the baskets had to be bent back so that they could fit. I am now at a crossroads with this thing. I cant utilize it for much (the slatted shelves make it useless) but is it worth the trouble of taking it apart and trying to fit it back in the box the right way?
customer_reviews.author: Rob

customer_reviews.title: have hardly any storage in my apartment and this is perfect!! it was very easy to assemble with ...
customer_reviews.text: fit perfectly in the hallway just outside my bathroom. have hardly any storage in my apartment and this is perfect!! it was very easy to assemble with the help of a friend (cuz its awkward with one person trying to steady it and put it together,)
customer_reviews.author: WinterPrincess

customer_reviews.title: I LOVE this. It isn't as small I pictured
customer_reviews.text: I was worried this would be too small and short. I LOVE this. It isn't as small I pictured. I was looking for something to place this rack on to lift, but since putting it together, I do not believe it needs to be lifted. There is a place for 12 bottles of wine. I am very happy with this rack!
customer_reviews.author: GMA

customer_reviews.title: Top shelves are not super sturdy. The support bars on the top bend ...
customer_reviews.text: Not deep enough for a small microwave unless you leave the decorative back panel off. Top shelves are not super sturdy. The support bars on the top bend significantly under anything more than 3lbs. We made a wood top for it to make it work better for our microwave and kuerig. Works great for our small kitchen by freeing up counter space.
customer_reviews.author: Alyson P.

customer_reviews.title: Well designed and attractive
customer_reviews.text: I’ve had this for months now and it held up through a move. I love this piece! It looks better than the pictures and is the perfect place to store extra kitchen equipment. Awesome!
customer_reviews.author: Deborah Capes

customer_reviews.title: Cute shelf, easy to put together!
customer_reviews.text: This is a lovely addition to my kitchen. Very simple to put together, it only took me about 20 minutes. And you only need to use the Allen wrench that they provided. You need more tools if you're going to anchor it to the wall, which I chose not to because I don't have small children in my house, but if you do, I would strongly recommend anchoring it to the wall because it's very lightweight. Love the item, definitely worth the money they charged.
customer_reviews.author: Lori S.

customer_reviews.title: Cute outdoor garden rack
customer_reviews.text: Used for backyard to store garden tools and garden items. Looks great.
customer_reviews.author: April Singleton

customer_reviews.title: Small and cute!
customer_reviews.text: Perfect for my small patio. Took 10 minutes to assemble. Look at the pictures first. Hides all my basic garden and sprinkler tools with the pretty pots on top.
customer_reviews.author: Daizy

customer_reviews.title: Handy catch-all!
customer_reviews.text: The assembly is easy, the rack is solid. Works great in our breezeway as a catch-all for dog leashes, hats, gloves, etc and a place to set whatever I'm carrying so I can unlock the door :-)
customer_reviews.author: D. Masselink

customer_reviews.title: Perfect for a small space
customer_reviews.text: Just what I needed. I put this up on my breakfast bar (which I never really used, except to collect clutter). I was able to take all my food canisters out of my pantry to make more room there. Easy to put together, too.
customer_reviews.author: Big Cat

customer_reviews.title: Nice looker
customer_reviews.text: It came with some of the shelves bent because they were poorly designed, but overall we really like this piece. We liked it so much that we bought the two matching ones. Warning though: the others are slightly different shades of metal color which was disappointing. It is cheaply made, but worth the money.
customer_reviews.author: kodiakcowboy

customer_reviews.title: Read the specs on size. I made it work and happy.
customer_reviews.text: I got this back in January. I looked at the specs and knew it was 32" tall. I somehow ordered it anyway. I did a little modification to lift it up 5" and it's great for the purpose I purchased it for. Plus I have storage space below. I love this unit.
customer_reviews.author: Phobbic

customer_reviews.title: Nice shelf for the money.
customer_reviews.text: It is easy to put together and pretty well built once you get it together. It a little lower than you would think. If you looking at this item pay attention to the measurements.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: love wine
customer_reviews.text: The rack is super strong and holds the bottles of wine perfectly. I have put a 10 gallon fish tank on top that is used as a terrarium and it looks amazing on it. Wish that it held more wine glasses, but other than that, it fits in perfectly exactly where we wanted it to. Definitely would recommend getting one!
customer_reviews.author: Jan R

customer_reviews.title: This is one of the best pieces of furniture I've bought
customer_reviews.text: This thing looks great and and awesomely functional. I couldn't be happier with it. Wife loves it too, so there's that.
customer_reviews.author: Stephen H.

customer_reviews.title: WELL worth the money!!!!
customer_reviews.text: Exactly as pictured, practical design, assembly easy and fast with clear directions, all necessary hardware and tool included. I wanted tis for a very narrow space, so I was thrilled dimensions were accurate. The airy design keeps it feeling light and casual, while the wine rack, baskets, shelves, and glass rack provide really efficient storage for quite a bit -- almost more like a buffet serving station. Seller shipped promptly, well packaged, not too heavy, no damage. This has been just about my most positive on-line buying experience, with really solid quality for a practical, decorative, and sturdy addition to my home.
customer_reviews.author: Rosalie Brown

customer_reviews.title: Very happy with this purchase!
customer_reviews.text: Love it! Just right size for where I need it. Lack of storage, small house and this organizer fits right in and it was easy and fast to put together. Stored a lot of little necessary items that I would normally leave on dining room table. And it looks real pretty!!
customer_reviews.author: Pichuza49

customer_reviews.title: Beautiful Piece!
customer_reviews.text: So I put this together in about 45 minutes. Very easy to assemble & looks great! A wonderful piece to display. Highly recommend to others!

customer_reviews.title: LOVE IT!!!!!

product_meta.title: SEI Furniture Celtic Wrought Iron Bakers Rack Wine Storage, Gunmetal Gray
product_meta.description: Elegant and beautiful, this bistro wine rack will help with storage, display, and organization all in one. Two rattan baskets function as removable drawers while two open shelves and a top rack are extremely versatile. A wine bottle rack for 12 and a set of glass holders make this bakers rack an ideal addition for any beginning wine connoisseur. Decorative scrollwork laces the top for a classic touch. Features 1 broad slatted workspace, 2 slatted shelves, 2 glassware racks, and 12 bottle holders total. This wonderful piece has a mixed materials composition. Dimensions include: Overall: 36.5" W x 11" D x 36" H; Top shelf: 35" W x 10" D; Open shelves: 13" W x 11" D x 14" H; Stemware rack: 9" D; Baskets: 11.5" W x 9.5" D x 8" H; Clearance: 35" W x 9.5" D x 4" HThis one-of-a-kind item approximately weighs 29 lbs and can support up to 20 pounds (top), 20 pounds (per shelf), 10 pounds (per basket). Only quality materials and manufacturing will do. Product materials include: Iron, rattan. Assembly: Required. Made in China.
